- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper discusses network analysis of mobility flows using bibliometric data. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is also likely as the paper uses bibliometric data for analysis. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses mobility networks at different levels of aggregation. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is less likely but still possible as the paper may touch on privacy concerns related to bibliometric data. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss methods for retrieving and analyzing bibliometric data.
